            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " image above ‚Äî from the ground up:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "We‚Äôre committing $5 million to support local journalists interested in starting or continuing their work on our new platform for independent writers which you can learn more about ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "here",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://www.facebook.com/formedia/supporting-independent-voices",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ".",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "quote",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "However, as a careful reading of the above quote will show, this is not a completely altruistic move (any more than Substack's is). Facebook ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "requires",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " you to use its tools as part of the deal. As always, I have questions about how portable Facebook-based subscriptions will be, and I'd always recommend that people take this money with their eyes firmly open to the degree to which it ties them a singular platform. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "paywall"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "As Emily Bell puts it:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "embed",
        "url": "https://twitter.com/emilybell/status/1387757673781813249?s=20",
        "html": "<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Substack started a local project, now FB moves in with $5m . Some local independent writers (those not in newsrooms) and their communities will hopefully benefit. But note that this is an incentivized fragmentation of the structure of local news. Platform-designed infrastructure <a href=\"https://t.co/RJ8C99DouO\">https://t.co/RJ8C99DouO</a></p>&mdash; emily bell (@emilybell) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/emilybell/status/1387757673781813249?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">April 29, 2021</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n",
        "metadata": {
          "url": "https://twitter.com/emilybell/status/1387757673781813249",
          "author_name": "emily bell",
          "author_url": "https://twitter.com/emilybell",
          "width": 550,
          "height": null,
          "cache_age": "3153600000",
          "provider_name": "Twitter",
          "provider_url": "http://www.twitter.com/",
          "version": "1.0"
        },
        "embedType": "rich"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "That said, the local news ecosystem generally needs innovation and experimentation, and if this initiative helps facilitate that, well, good. And, as many YouTubers have proved down the years, you might start off with a revenue stream built around a single platform, but once you have an audience, you can diversify. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "bookmark",
        "url": "https://www.reuters.com/article/facebook-journalism-idUSL1N2MM01C",
        "metadata": {
          "url": "https://www.reuters.com/article/facebook-journalism-idUSL1N2MM01C",
          "title": "Facebook to pay $5 mln to local journalists in newsletter push",
          "description": "Facebook Inc said Thursday it will give $5 million to pay local journalists in multi-year deals as part of its new publishing platform to help independent writers attract an audience and make money through the social media network.",
          "author": "Sheila Dang",
          "publisher": "Reuters",
