            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " back in my teenage years (which does explain a lot). One thing that has always stuck with me is the idea explored in one episode that, if you can't counter someone's ideas, attack the person instead: play the man, not the ball, as the TV show put it. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "It's a useful filter to examine how people behave on social media through, such as this attack by Glenn Greenwald on James Ball:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "embed",
        "url": "https://twitter.com/ggreenwald/status/1388829792640901125?s=20",
        "html": "<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">This is a vivid mirror into these large corporate sites. James Ball never broke a story of any significance: let alone the Pulitzer-winning NSA reporting I did or the Brazil expos√©s (which his own paper heralded). Nobody reads him, so they use this framework to beg for prestige. <a href=\"https://t.co/NIxEolhQeW\">pic.twitter.com/NIxEolhQeW</a></p>&mdash; Glenn Greenwald (@ggreenwald) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/ggreenwald/status/1388829792640901125?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">May 2, 2021</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n",
        "metadata": {
          "url": "https://twitter.com/ggreenwald/status/1388829792640901125",
          "author_name": "Glenn Greenwald",
          "author_url": "https://twitter.com/ggreenwald",
